Public Defender's office is actively looking for counsel.

9:03 a.m.  Defendant Christopher L. Dominick in court, in custody.  Attorney Jedidiah J Dodge in court for State of Wisconsin.  Attorney Taylor O Soule in court for Christopher L. Dominick. 
Cases heard today are 22CF102 & 22CM56 for Final Pretrial and cases tracking are 21CM246 & 21CM365 for Pre-Trial.

Court calls the cases.
ADA Dodge states the appearances.

Court will not be focusing on 21CM246 & 21CM365 as they are only set for a Pre-Trial.
Court states that in preparing for today's hearing she noticed document #31 that had been filed by her client and she questions Atty Soule and she is aware that he had filed this document and
Atty Soule states that she will not be addressing this issue today.
Defendant is informed that he has very good counsel representing him and is informed that he should not be filing documents pro se due to the fact that he does have counsel representing him.
Court states case law on the record.
Document #31 will not be addressed by the Court today.
Court questions the defendant if he has any questions; he states he does but he will not get into it.

**Motion for Joinder will be heard first.
ADA Dodge is in agreement to address the Motion for Joinder and Atty Soule is in agreement as well.
Court has reviewed the brief's of both parties for the Motion for Joinder.
9:09 a.m.  ADA Dodge puts additional information on the record for this Motion for Joinder that he had filed.
ADA Dodge states that the Court should grant the Motion for Joinder on 22CF102 & 22CM56 as this would be administratively appropriate.
9:12 a.m.  Atty Soule is in opposition to the Motion for Joinder and states her reasons on the record.
Atty Soule would ask that the State's Motion be Denied.
Court informs ADA Dodge that his motion was filed under 871.21 and feels that this may be a typo and that he may have meant to use 971.12; ADA Dodge 
makes statements and does indicate that the 871.21 is incorrect.  ADA Dodge is informed by the Court that he needs to make sure his statues are listed correctly.
Statute 971.12 is stated on the record by the Court.
Court informs ADA Dodge that 22CM56 should have been filed as charges in 22CF102 and states her reasons why on the record.

BY THE COURT:
Motion for Joinder is GRANTED due to Judicial Economy.
Atty Soule is granted the reservation to move the court for severance of the 2 cases that had just been joined if anything new comes up.

Letter from ADA Dodge to the Court with regards to outstanding discovery dated 07/01/22 and one that had been filed on 06/01/22.
Court questions ADA Dodge with regards to discovery and he responds to indicate that all discovery had been turned over to Atty Soule.
Atty Soule believes that she had received all discovery from the State and makes a record of this.
Atty Soule states that she is still waiting on a transcript from the revocation hearing and that is is taking an extreme amount of time to get this transcript and she will turn this over to the State once 
she receives this transcript.
Court further questions Atty Soule; she responds.
ADA Dodge will not make a record of this transcript at this time.

BY THE COURT:
By end of the day on August 5, 2022 all parties are to have done some research on the topic stated on the record with regards to the revocation transcript and testimony and the parties
are to provide the court something in writing with regards to this.  Per the Court a letter brief is appropriate for the parties to file.

Motions in Limine to be heard as well as the jury instructions.
Court makes a record of the jury instructions to the parties and states that both cases should be included.
Parties are to review the jury instructions within the next day or so and they are to email with a reply all to Branch 3 Judicial Assistant as to what the take an issue with and they will not have to spend a lot of 
time on this at the time of trial.

Jury witness list is put on the record for the parties.
ADA Dodge's witness list field in April 2022 will be the one he is using.
Atty Soule states that her witness list is also complete that she filed on 06/30/22.

Motions in Limine filed by the defense.
Atty Soule objects to note taking by the jurors.

Court will begin with the State's Motions in Limine -
#1 - no objection - GRANTED
#2 - no objection - GRANTED 
#3 - Only 2 witnesses have prior convictions - parties are in agreement
Court goes through the # of convictions for the witnesses and stats these individually on the record
Defendant convictions are stipulated by the parties to be 15 - if he decides to testify the parties are able to ask him the # of convictions and he is to respond "15"
#4 - ADA Dodge makes additional record & Atty Soule has no further comment
GRANTED
#5 - no objection - GRANTED
#6 - ADA Dodge makes additional record & Atty Soule makes her additional record (should be addressed at trial, if it comes up)
DECISION AT TRIAL 
#7 - ADA Dodge makes additional record & Atty Soule makes her additional record (should be addressed at trial, if it comes up)
DECISION AT TRIAL 
#8 - should not have been included ADA Dodge will be withdrawing #8 & Atty Soule has no comment
WITHDRAWN
#9 - no objection - GRANTED
#10 - ADA Dodge makes additional record & Atty Soule has no objection and states her reasons on the record
no objection - GRANTED
#11 - no objection - GRANTED
#12 - Court questions the Ludwig Colloquy - ADA Dodge has no comment
Atty Soule is not sure what this is - Court explains
Court questions defendant if he understands all offers that had been made to him up to this point - he responds
If is defendant's request to go to trial at this time.

Court will begin with the Defendant's Motions in Limine -
#1 - Court puts the order on the record
#2 - GRANTED 
#3 - Atty Soule has no additional record & ADA Dodge makes a record/Atty Soule responds to ADA Dodge's record
GRANTED
#4 - GRANTED
#5 - Atty Soule makes additional record & ADA Dodge has no record 
GRANTED
#6 - GRANTED 
#7 - ?
#8 - Atty Soule has no additional record & ADA Dodge makes additional record
Court questions ADA Dodge with regards to victims rights
Only victim is the mother of the defendant - victim witness coordinator is to be altered if the mother of the defendant is called by the defense.
This is to be addressed the morning of trial
GRANTED - victim witness addressed at trial
#9 - Atty Soule makes a record & ADA Dodge has no record
GRANTED 
#10 - Atty Soule makes her record on the prohibition of note taking & ADA Dodge makes a record and would ask that the note taking be allowed
Court takes this UNDER ADVISEMENT - Court will need to take time to think about this and reflect on it
Court will do some research & let the parties know the morning of trial
#11 - Atty Soule makes additional record & ADA Dodge has no objection 
GRANTED

Court believes that this covers everything that needed to be addressed today.
Court will let the parties know the morning of trial the issues that had been discussed today.
Court will allow for one alternate, so 13 jurors with 5 strikes each.
